'''Ask.fm'''為於2010年6月16日在[[拉脫維亞|拉脫維亞]][[里加|里加]]建立的社交網站<ref name="Kenins"/> ，於2014年8月被[[Ask.com|Ask.com]]購入。它是{{link-en|Formspring|Formspring}}的主要競爭對手，但以全球使用量來說卻已經遠遠超越前者。

== 特色 ==
Ask.fm能夠隨意的使用註冊用戶或匿名用戶的身份詢問問題，而被提問者亦能根據自己的意願是否回答問題<ref>{{cite web|title=Safety tips|url=http://ask.fm/about/safety|publisher=Ask.fm|accessdate=14 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217024556/http://ask.fm/about/safety|archivedate=2014年2月17日}}</ref>。

該網站也為用戶提供安全提示，為用戶提供有關「聰明與怎樣負責任的發言」的基本指針<ref>{{cite web|title=How does Ask.fm work?|url=http://ask.fm/about/safety/safety-security-essentials|publisher=Ask.fm|accessdate=14 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141214101029/http://ask.fm/about/safety/safety-security-essentials|archivedate=2014年12月14日}}</ref>。

== 批評 ==
[[File:Ask.fm_Logo.png|250px]]
在2013年中期，該網站為寫有大量網絡欺凌的媒體文章之一的網站，並且間接使某些人自殺<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2261588/Ask-fm-Pupils-parents-warned-social-networking-website-linked-teen-abuse.html |title=Pupils and parents warned social networking website linked to teen abuse |newspaper=Daily Mail |first=Martin |last=Beckford |date=13 January 2013 |accessdate=7 August 2013 |archive-date=2016-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011220329/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2261588/Ask-fm-Pupils-parents-warned-social-networking-website-linked-teen-abuse.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他們自殺的原因主要是許多匿名用戶廣泛傳播訊息。不過，Ask.fm後來回應指控稱：「我們有一個舉報的功能，並且聘請了一批版主打擊網絡欺凌。」。除此之外，Ask.fm也有一些監管著「露骨的評論」的版主。但是就算如此也從來沒有一個評論被徹底刪除，即使是明顯的威脅或恐嚇。這也是Ask.fm被批評的原因之一<ref name="arcticstartup">{{cite web |url=http://www.arcticstartup.com/2013/05/13/ask-fm-responds-to-cyberbullying-allegations |first=Dmitri |last=Sarle |date=13 May 2013 |accessdate=14 December 2014 |title=Ask.fm Responds To Cyberbullying |publisher=[[ArcticStartup|ArcticStartup]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130816225007/http://www.arcticstartup.com/2013/05/13/ask-fm-responds-to-cyberbullying-allegations |archivedate=2013年8月16日 }}</ref>。

據2013年8月6日的報導，一個來自[[萊斯特郡|萊斯特郡]]的14歲女孩漢娜·史密斯（Hannah Smith）自殺身亡，她的父親指她在生前曾經受到來自Ask.fm用戶的欺凌。並呼籲對如Ask.fm等社交網站採取更嚴格的監管<ref>{{cite news|title=Hannah Smith death: Father says daughter was victim of cyberbullies|first=Hannah|last=Smith|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-leicestershire-23584769|date=6 August 2013|accessdate=14 December 2014|archive-date=2014-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141125075528/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-leicestershire-23584769|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Shute |first=Joe |title=Cyberbullying suicides: What will it take to have Ask.fm shut down? |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/health/children_shealth/10225846/Cyberbullying-suicides-What-will-it-take-to-have-Ask.fm-shut-down.html |accessdate=6 August 2013 |newspaper=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6IgGQlySe?url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/health/children_shealth/10225846/Cyberbullying-suicides-What-will-it-take-to-have-Ask.fm-shut-down.html |archivedate=2013-08-06 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。後來史密斯一家響應之前因同樣原因而自殺，來自[[蘭開夏郡|蘭開夏郡]]{{link-en|葛斯洛格|Goosnargh}}的15歲青少年約書亞·昂斯沃斯（Joshua Unsworth）的父母呼籲封鎖Ask.fm的活動<ref>[http://www.lep.co.uk/news/local/joshua-unsworth-s-parents-call-for-ban-on-notorious-website-ask-fm-1-5931924 Joshua Unsworth's parents call for ban on notorious website ask.fm] {{Wayback|url=http://www.lep.co.uk/news/local/joshua-unsworth-s-parents-call-for-ban-on-notorious-website-ask-fm-1-5931924 |date=20141011190118 }} Lancashire Evening Post</ref>。而Ask.fm則回應：「樂意幫助警方」<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1124978/hannah-smith-suicide-father-attacks-ask-fm|title=Hannah Smith: Ask.fm 'Happy To Help Police'|date=6 August 2013|accessdate=14 December 2014|work=Sky News}}</ref>。因應漢娜·史密斯的自殺，英國首相[[大衛·卡梅倫|大衛·卡梅倫]]要求抵制不採取措施應對網絡欺凌的網站<ref>{{cite news|last=Coyne|first=Ellen|title=Cyberbullying websites should be boycotted, says Cameron|url=http://www.theguardian.com/society/2013/aug/08/cyberbullying-websites-boycotted-david-cameron|accessdate=9 August 2013|newspaper=Guardian|date=14 December 2014|archive-date=2014-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141013022714/http://www.theguardian.com/society/2013/aug/08/cyberbullying-websites-boycotted-david-cameron|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一些廣告商的反應是終止與Afk.fm的聯繫，包括[[救助儿童会|救助儿童会]]<ref name="BR 130809">{{cite news |last=Chapman |first=Matthew |title=Save the Children leads ad boycott of Ask.fm following suicide tragedy |url=http://www.brandrepublic.com/bulletin/brandrepublicnewsbulletin/article/1194488/save-children-leads-ad-boycott-askfm-following-suicide-tragedy/?DCMP=EMC-CONBrandRepublicdailynewsbulletin |accessdate=9 August 2013 |newspaper=Brand Republic |date=14 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130816193608/http://www.brandrepublic.com/bulletin/brandrepublicnewsbulletin/article/1194488/save-children-leads-ad-boycott-askfm-following-suicide-tragedy/?DCMP=EMC-CONBrandRepublicdailynewsbulletin |archivedate=2013-08-16 }}</ref>、[[eBay|eBay]]和[[英國電信|英國電信]]。而[[沃達豐|沃達豐]]則早已終止在Ask.fm上買廣告<ref name="BR 130809" />。

